## Development Guidelines

### Code Quality Standards
- Write correct, best practice code
- Apply DRY principle (Don't Repeat Yourself)
- Bug-free and fully functional
- Complete implementation (no TODOs or placeholders)
- Prioritize readability over performance

### Code Implementation Rules

#### General
- Use early returns for readability
- Always use Tailwind classes (no CSS or style tags)
- Always use Composition API
- Complete all imports
- Proper component naming

#### Naming Conventions
- Descriptive variable and function names
- Event handlers prefixed with "handle" (e.g., `handleClick`, `handleKeyDown`)
- Use `const` for functions: `const toggle = () => {}`
- Define types when possible

## Communication Style
- Be concise
- Minimize unnecessary prose
- Acknowledge uncertainty when unsure
- Never guess - state "I don't know" if uncertain
